@node @t{gatbps} Options
@chapter @t{gatbps} Options

Each option has
one or more names, and each
name is either long or short@.
Each long name consists of two
hyphen-minus characters followed by
zero or more printable characters except
for the space and equals sign characters,
and each short name consists of one hyphen-minus
character followed by one printable character
except for the space and hyphen-minus characters@.
Each option either requires a value,
permits a value, or forbids a value@.

Let
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L}}
and
@w{@t{-}@i{S}}
be long and short names for an option and
@w{@i{V}}
be a value@.
If the option
requires a value,
then it may be written as either
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L}@t{=}@i{V}@comma{}}
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L@w{ }V}@comma{}}
@w{@t{-}@i{SV}@comma{}}
or
@w{@t{-}@i{S@w{ }V}@.}
If the option
permits a value,
then it may be written as either
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L}@t{=}@i{V}@comma{}}
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L}@comma{}}
@w{@t{-}@i{SV}@comma{}}
or
@w{@t{-}@i{S}@.}
If the option
forbids a value,
then it may be written as either
@w{@t{-@w{-}}@i{L}}
or
@w{@t{-}@i{S}@comma{}}
and in the latter case
it may be combined with an
immediately following argument in
(combined) short form by deleting the
@w{@t{-}@i{S}}
argument and inserting the
@w{@i{S}}
character into the following
argument just after the leading
@w{@t{-}}
character@.

The following options are supported:

@table @asis
@item @w{@t{-@w{-}}}
@include ipez.texi
The
@w{@t{-@w{-}}}
option disables option detection,
causing all remaining arguments
to be interpreted as operands@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}all}[@t{=}@i{V}]}
@itemx @w{@t{-a}[@i{V}]}
@include ipez.texi
The
@w{@t{-@w{-}all}}
option prepends
all special files to
the remaining arguments@.
Each is prefixed with
@w{@i{V}@.}
If
@w{@i{V}}
is not empty and does not
end with a slash character, then
a slash character is appended to
@w{@i{V}@.}
If
@w{@i{V}}
is omitted, then
@w{@i{V}}
is taken to be empty@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}help}[@t{=}@i{S}]}
@include ipez.texi
The
@w{@t{-@w{-}help}}
option writes text to standard output and
causes all further arguments to be ignored@.
If
@w{@i{S}}
is not given, then
the text is a short description of the program@.
Otherwise, the text is a short description
of the file that would be generated by the
@w{@t{gatbps@w{ }-@w{-}@w{ }}@i{S}}
command@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}man}}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}man}
option writes text to standard output
and causes all further arguments to be ignored@.
The text is the source code of the program's
manual page, which can be processed with any
command that is analogous to the
@t{tbl@w{ }|@w{ }nroff@w{ }-man}
command@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}recursive}}
@itemx @t{-r}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}recursive}
option enables recursive dependency
generation, which is initially disabled@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}style}[@t{=}@i{S}]}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}style}
option is replaced by the
@t{-@w{-}style=always}
option@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style=}@i{S}
option is replaced by the
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=}@i{S}
and
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=}@i{S}
options@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}style-stderr}[@t{=}@i{S}]}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr}
option is replaced by the
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=always}
option@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=}@i{S}
option enables or disables bold,
underline, and color styling of
text written to standard error,
which is initially disabled@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=always}
option enables it@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=auto}
option enables it if standard error
is associated with a terminal
or disables it if not@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stderr=}@i{S}
option with any other
@i{S}
disables it@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}style-stdout}[@t{=}@i{S}]}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout}
option is replaced by the
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=always}
option@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=}@i{S}
option enables or disables bold,
underline, and color styling of
text written to standard output,
which is initially disabled@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=always}
option enables it@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=auto}
option enables it if standard output
is associated with a terminal
or disables it if not@.
The
@t{-@w{-}style-stdout=}@i{S}
option with any other
@i{S}
disables it@.

@item @w{@t{-@w{-}version}}
@include ipez.texi
The
@t{-@w{-}version}
option writes text to standard output
and causes all further arguments to be ignored@.
The text is the program's
name, package, version number,
release date, and copyright information@.
@end table
